@database "MaxManager - Known bugs"

@NODE Main "MaxManager - Known bugs"

  @{b}@{u}Known bugs in MaxManager@{ub}@{uu}


  As every program, MaxManager is not perfect (yet :-) and due to
 development process got some @{b}known@{ub} bug unfixed. Below you can
 find the list of them and solutions how to workaroud them harmless
 until I fix them. All listed bugs are not critical and won't cause
 system crash nor database damage, but may be annoyoing. Sorry.


 * @{u}Section To Drawer Attachments@{uu}

 The bugs appears while you want to remove the path from inside the
 list while having some attachments made makes MaxManager to mess all
 already set attachments. The only safe workaround so far is to detach
 all attachments and then remove the section.
 

 * @{u}Pathes@{uu}

 It's rather required to end all non temporary pathes (e.g. in program
 settings) with colon or trailing slash depending on path itself. In
 some cases it's required by MAX's (e.g. when you add new path with
 Prefs/Pathes/Attachment editor - take care it ends with "/", or ":")

 Problems with pathes may sometimes appears when using ASL filerequesters
 to change existing paths. Sometimes there's part of old path left
 in the result string (it doesn't happen when there's "/" or ":" at the
 end).

 Finaly MaxManager will care about this, but for now it can sometimes
 ommit these sitation, which may drive to small problems.

@endnode
